## 6. Plan Files

Plans live inside each service repo under `.agentbus-plans/`:

```
payments-service/
└── .agentbus-plans/
    ├── 001-kafka-migration.md
    ├── 002-webhook-redesign.md
    └── 003-auth-refactor.md
```

### Naming convention

```
<NNN>-<feature-slug>.md
```

- `NNN` — zero-padded 3-digit auto-incremented index
- `feature-slug` — lowercase, hyphenated, derived from the feature description

The orchestrator calls `next_plan_number.py` inside each service repo to get the next available number before writing.

### `write_plan.py`

```
uv run write_plan.py <service-path> <feature-slug> <plan-content-file>
```

Computes the next plan number, creates `.agentbus-plans/` if missing, writes the file.

### `read_plan.py`

```
uv run read_plan.py                  # reads latest plan in current dir
uv run read_plan.py --plan 002       # reads plan 002
```

Prints plan content to stdout.
Recommended extensions:
- `--list` to enumerate plans and status
- `--path` to print only selected plan path (for safe in-place refinement)

