## 8. Acceptance Criteria (v0.4 — Evidence-Based)

### Scenario 1 — Wave 1: Service Mapping

Given: three services (`payments-service`, `notifications-service`, `crm-service`) without AGENTS.md
When: orchestrator runs Wave 1
Then:
- Each service gets `AGENTS.md` written at repo root
- AGENTS.md includes: stack, architecture, components, APIs, DB, testing
- Orchestrator workspace gets `service-outputs/{service}.json` summaries
- status.json shows wave 1 complete, wave 2 ready

### Scenario 2 — Wave 2: Plan Refinement

Given: Wave 1 complete, AGENTS.md exists in all services
When: orchestrator runs Wave 2
Then:
- Each service gets `.agentbus-plans/001-feature.md` written
- PLAN.md includes: overview, changes, testing, dependencies, rollback
- Subagents read their own AGENTS.md during refinement
- status.json shows wave 2 complete, wave 3 ready

### Scenario 3 — Wave 3: Verification

Given: Wave 2 complete, PLAN.md exists in all services
When: orchestrator runs Wave 3
Then:
- Each service gets `.agentbus-plans/001-feature-REPORT.md` written
- REPORT.md includes: status, checklist, files, risks, cross-service impact
- Subagents read related service plans for dependency checking
- Orchestrator reads all REPORTs and verifies consistency

### Scenario 4 — Global Verification

Given: Wave 3 complete, all REPORTs written
When: orchestrator runs global verification
Then:
- Checks: all ready, dependencies mirrored, contracts consistent
- Writes: `PLAN.md`, `TEST-PLAN.md`, `DEPLOY-ORDER.md` in orchestrator workspace
- Reports: readiness status, issues, next steps

### Scenario 5 — Retry After Failure

Given: Wave 2 failed for `notifications-service` (error in status.json)
When: developer fixes issue and re-runs orchestrator for Wave 2
Then:
- Only `notifications-service` subagent re-runs
- PLAN.md gets overwritten with corrected plan
- status.json updated to reflect success
- Other services unchanged

### Scenario 6 — Add Service Mid-Flight

Given: Wave 2 complete for services A, B
When: developer adds service C and re-runs Wave 2
Then:
- status.json updated with new service
- Only service C gets Wave 1 and Wave 2 processing
- A and B remain unchanged

### Scenario 7 — Orchestrator ask mode (no write)

Given: three services with README.md
When: `/agentbus-orchestrator --ask "how does onboarding work?" payments notifications crm`
Then:
- Orchestrator reads docs across services
- Returns cross-service answer
- No files written (no status.json, no AGENTS.md updates)

