## 9. Failure Modes and Recovery

| Case | Expected behavior |
|---|---|
| Service not registered | Skip service, include in final report with reason `service-not-registered` |
| Docs unavailable | Wave 1 subagent creates AGENTS.md from scratch by exploring codebase |
| Subagent fails mid-wave | Update status.json with error, report to user, allow retry |
| Retry wave | Re-run subagent for failed service only, overwrite artifacts |
| Add service mid-flight | Update status.json, mark new service as "pending" for current wave |
| Invalid slug | Normalize to kebab-case or fail with clear validation error |
| REPORT.md missing for review | Review skill reports "missing report for {service}" |
| Dependency not mirrored | Review skill flags inconsistency, suggests re-running wave |

## 10. Evidence-Based Workflow Benefits

| Aspect | Old (v0.3) | New (v0.4) |
|---|---|---|
| State management | Accumulated in orchestrator context | Written to files, read on demand |
| Communication | Data returned in responses | Artifacts written, paths returned |
| Resume capability | Limited | Full — re-read status.json and continue |
| Auditability | Plan files only | Full chain: AGENTS → PLAN → REPORT |
| Reusability | Plans per feature | AGENTS.md reusable for future features |
| Parallelism | Sequential | Parallel within waves via Task tool |

